II. ELASTIC OPTICAL NETWORKS
The EONs based on OFDM consist of bandwidth-variable transponders (BVTs) and bandwidth-variable wavelength cross connects (BV-WXCs), as shown fig. 1. The BV-WXC is used to establish a lightpath by a cross-connection with the appropriate spectrum bandwidth. The BVT is used to tune the bandwidth by adjusting the transmission data rate or modulation level. The high-speed transmission is supported by BVTs with high modulation level for short distance lightpaths. Meanwhile, low modulation level is used to extend the transmission reach. Table I represents the relationship of spectrum efficiency and transmission reach for various modulation formats [3].

