B. Fuzzy Rule Base The output of fuzzy logic control system is the crisp value
for the condition of available spectrum blocks. The output membership function consists of three triangles and two trapezoid-type fuzzy set: very good (VG), good (G), medium (M), bad (B), very bad (VB), as shown fig. 6. All the membership values will be lies in between 0 to 1.

664

Fig. 6. Output membership function

To define the relationship of the inputs and output, we compose the Mamdani-type fuzzy rule base. The proposed SA algorithm uses nine fuzzy rules, as shown Table II.

